<p>Let's assume that I have simple class:</p>  <pre><code>   public class Test     {        @Path("/test")        @POST        @Produces(APPLICATION_JSON)        @Consumes(APPLICATION_JSON)        public TestResponse post(TestResponse request, @HeaderParam("text") String text)        {           return new TestResponse(request.getData());        }     } </code></pre>  <p>and I want to test this class. So how I can param in code like this:</p>  <pre><code> Entity&lt;TestRequest&gt; requestEntity = Entity.entity(request, MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);  final TestResponse response =  target("test").request().post(requestEntity, TestResponse.class); </code></pre>